text:
LAW NOTICES.—This Day.

VICE-CHANCELLOR'S COURT, LINCOLN'S-INN.
Sittings at ten.

Preece v Barrow, motion per order; after which, the first side of petitions from the last printed list of the 21st—Muscofield v Muscofield, restored.

BANKRUPTCY COURT, BASINGHALL-STREET.
Before Mr. Commissioner Merivale.

W. C. Empson, of Leamington-priors, Warwickshire, money-lender, at eleven; audit—George Teller, of Phoenix Wharf, City Basin, coal merchant, at eleven, adjourned dividend—William Parker, of the Steel yard, Upper Thames street, lead-merchant, at twelve, audit and dividend—George Claby, of Hungerford market, corn dealer and seedman, at one; audit—John Deacon, of Berners-street, Oxford-street, upholsterer, at half past one; audit

Before Mr. Commissioner Fane.

John Mealey, of Cranbourne-street, Leicester square, fringe-manufacturer, at eleven; audit—R. B. Bender, of South-street, Grosvenor-square, wine merchant and tailor, at one, choice of assignees—Abraham Moore, of Wells-row, Islington, builder, at two, choice of assignees.

Before Mr. Commissioner Holroyd.

John Shields, of Bridge-row, Lambeth, wire worker, at eleven, dividend—John Wells, of St. James's-place, tailor, at twelve; dividend—Moffatt and Brown, of Goswell-street, blue-makers, at one, dividend.

ECCLESIASTICAL COURTS.
[Sittings in Michaelmas Term, 1835.]

ARCHES COURT.
1st Session, Monday, Nov. 4.
2nd Session, Wednesday, Nov. 13.
3rd Session, Wednesday, Nov. 19.

ADMIRALTY COURT.
1st Session, Thursday, Nov. 6.
2nd Session, Thursday, Nov. 12.
3rd Session, Thursday, Nov. 19.

PREROGATIVE COURT.
1st Session, Friday, Nov. 6.
2nd Session, Saturday, Nov. 14.
3rd Session, Saturday, Nov. 21.

APPEALS.
1st Session, Saturday, Nov. 7.
2nd Session, Monday, Nov. 16.
3rd Session, Tuesday, Nov. 24.

CONSISTORY COURT.
1st Session, Tuesday, Nov. 10.
2nd Session, Tuesday, Nov. 17.
3rd Session, Wednesday, Nov. 25.

Caveat Day—Prerogative—Wednesday, Dec. 30.
Extra Court Day—Consistory—Wednesday, Dec. 30.
Default Day—Admiralty—Thursday, Dec. 31.
